The service at this hotel is great - on par with luxury hotels we've stayed at (Peninsula, Four Seasons).	I would reccomend this hotel to families that need to travel by train in Barcelona and people who want to enjoy a relaxing and luxury holiday.	On a plus point, the hotel is very central, but at the expense of any kind of luxuries.	No restaurant but this gives you every reason to explore excellent restaurants literally on your doorstep for evening meals - "pulpo" and "provenza" are opposite and provide great food at great prices.	This means that you are either under the comforter or exposed, this is hard for me to regulate my sleeping comfort temperature.